            <abstract label="Abstract:">This collection traces the history of food, cookery, agriculture, kitchen equipment, and more through hundreds of advertising trade cards from the second half of the 19th century.</abstract>
            <langmaterial label="Language:">Collection material in <language encodinganalog="041" langcode="eng">English</language>
            </langmaterial>
    </did>
    <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
            <head altrender="biography" id="a2">BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE </head>
            <p>In 1983 Nach Waxman opened the New York City book store Kitchen Arts &amp; Letters, specializing in cookbooks, gastronomy, and food books and magazines from across the world.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
            <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
                  <p>This collection traces the history of food, cookery, agriculture, kitchen equipment, and more through hundreds of advertising trade cards from the second half of the 19th century.</p>
    </scopecontent>
